verbose_text: In this study higher baseline levels of high sensitivity C-reactive protein (hsCRP), but not tumor necrosis factor receptor 2 (TNFR2), a membrane receptor that also binds TNF-alpha, were associated with an accelerated age related decline in measured GFR in the general population.
evidence: levels of high sensitivity C-reactive protein (hsCRP), but not tumor necrosis factor receptor 2
